Curiously enough, I was re-reading that section yesterday and marked that
equation with an exclamation point.

The initial assumption is that gravity attracts photons. How do we know
this?

We know that EM waves contain energy. And there is a mass-energy
relationship -- E equals M C squared. And THAT seems to requires that there
be some form of &quot;distributed mass&quot; in a region containing EM. Is that
&quot;distributed mass&quot; what we call a photon? I don't know.

